The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

P&P Update:

1. Changed RedHat OS from 7.2 to 7.3 for testing from WW51.

2. Changed CPU from QL66(VIS) to QLJ6(VIS) for performance test from WW50.

3. Changed Memory from 32GB 2400MHz to 32GB 2666MHz for Performance test from WW48.

4. Run NLB with Linux kernel 4.7.0, other tests are running with Linux Kernel 3.10.0

5. Runing NLB GBS mode 0 lpbk1 to exercise 2 sockets simultaneously for NLB loading power test.

6. Target for all test items are not ready, But OSS need target to generate report, so we just use WW43\'s data as target.

7. FPGA power workload: NLB

8. Core performance workloads: Mlc, Linpack, Stream.

WW01: 

a) No regression issue found.

b) For HSD[5345552] [2016_WW46 BKC][BIOS 108.D11][P&P][Neon City FPGA] Mlc Local all read memory peak Bandwidth decreased 13.74% (from 182.9 GB/s to 157.6 GB/s )

        -->Verify with B0 VIS QL66 CPU, the regression is 1.72%, cause the change list 435688 has much impact on B0 ES2 QLGZ CPU only, so downgrade this HSD to medium. and wait for H0 CPU to verify.

c) For HSD[5345776] [2016_WW53 BKC][BMC 79.19.r10365][P&P][Neon City FPGA] System idel power increased 7.58%(from 201.97W to 217.27W)

           and HSD [5345777] [2016_WW53 BKC][BMC 79.19.r10365][P&P][Neon City FPGA] MP Linpack score decreased 2.15%(from 1419.16 to1388.65)

        -->Verify with BMC 79.20.r10373, the system power is 200.01W and the MP linpack score is 1450, issues have been fixed with this BMC, close this sighting.
